Trigger The wight is reduced to 0 Hit Points.

Effect The wight makes a Strike before being destroyed. It doesn't gain any temporary HP from drain life on this Strike.

When the wight damages a living creature with its claw Strike, the wight gains [[/r 3 #Temporary Hit Points]]{3 temporary Hit Points} and the creature must succeed at a @Check[type:fortitude|dc:17] save or become @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.4D2KBtexWXa6oUMR]{Drained 1}. Further damage dealt by the wraith increases the amount of drain by 1 on a failed save to a maximum of drained 4.

A living humanoid slain by a wight's claw Strike rises as a @Compendium[pf2e.pathfinder-bestiary.ZPjQkKVMi3xoPcU0]{Wight Spawn} after [[/br 1d4 #Wight Spawn Transformation]]{1d4 rounds}. This wight spawn is under the command of the wight that killed it. It doesn't have Drain Life or Wight Spawn and becomes @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.i3OJZU2nk64Df3xm]{Clumsy 2} for as long as it is a wight spawn. If the creator of the wight spawn dies, the wight spawn becomes a full-fledged, autonomous wight; it regains its free will, gains Drain Life and Wight Spawn, and is no longer clumsy.
This one-handed curved blade is sharp on one side.
This smaller bow is made of a single piece of wood and favored by skirmishers and cavalry.
These projectiles are the ammunition for bows. The shaft of an arrow is made of wood. It is stabilized in flight by fletching at one end and bears a metal head on the other.

(arcane, evocation) If a creature passes the middle pair of pillars, both doors leading out of the room slam shut and lock; while the trap is active, the doors must be battered open with a successful @Check[type:athletics|dc:23|name:Batter Open Door] check or sufficient damage (Hardness 12; HP 48 [BT 24]). One of the starknife carvings glows with light, detaches from the pillar, and then flies outward, making a magical starknife Ranged Strike against a random creature within range. The trap then rolls initiative with its Stealth modifier of +12.
@Localize[PF2E.NPC.Abilities.Glossary.Darkvision]
An object shedding magical light (such as from the @Compendium[pf2e.spells-srd.WBmvzNDfpwka3qT4]{Light} spell) is treated as magical when used to attack the shadow.

When a creature's shadow is pulled free by Steal Shadow, it becomes a @Compendium[pf2e.pathfinder-bestiary.XrmHgbKgcHDi4OnK]{Shadow Spawn} under the command of the shadow that created it. This shadow spawn doesn't have Steal Shadow and is perpetually and incurably @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.i3OJZU2nk64Df3xm]{Clumsy 2}. If the creature the shadow spawn was pulled from dies, the shadow spawn becomes a full-fledged, autonomous shadow. If the creature recovers from its @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.MIRkyAjyBeXivMa7]{Enfeeblement}, its shadow returns to it and the shadow spawn is extinguished.
The shadow can @Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.XMcnh4cSI32tljXa]{Hide} or end its @Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.VMozDqMMuK5kpoX4]{Sneak} in a creature's or object's shadow.

Requirement The shadow hit a living creature with a shadow hand Strike on its previous action.

Effect The shadow pulls at the target's shadow, making the creature @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.MIRkyAjyBeXivMa7]{Enfeebled 1}. This is cumulative with other enfeebled conditions from shadows, to a maximum of enfeebled 4. If this increases a creature's enfeebled value to 3 or more, the target's shadow is separated from its body. Enfeebled from Steal Shadow decreases by 1 every hour.

dr.exceptions: except force, ghost touch, and positive; double resistance vs. non-magical

description.value: You have fewer actions. Slowed always includes a value. When you regain your actions at the start of your turn, reduce the number of actions you regain by your slowed value. Because slowed has its effect at the start of your turn, you don't immediately lose actions if you become slowed during your turn.
Requirement The zombie has a creature @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.kWc1fhmv9LBiTuei]{Grabbed} or @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.VcDeM8A5oI6VqhbM]{Restrained}.
